<paragraph id="8BC75722984F7053C5CDFA34FEB4F9EE" blockId="28.[136,1452,1462,2087]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Thallus saxicolous, rigid, erect, up to 
<quantity id="4C80FAC7984F7053C772FA34FDBDFA61" box="[567,623,1462,1489]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
long, pale yellow, older parts often discolored, with a distinct, delimited holdfast. Branches striate, filamentous, irregular, more or less terete, 0.8–1.0 mm broad, with numerous soralia producing ecorticate granules. Pseudocyphellae linear, longitudinally arranged. Cortical tissue paraplectenchymatous, 70–155 µm thick, peripheral tissue prosoplectenchymatous, 270–285 µm thick, medulla dense. Pycnidia not seen. Apothecia not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC75722984F7053C5F8F9E4FB68F930" blockId="28.[136,1452,1462,2087]" box="[189,1210,1638,1664]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C5F8F9E4FEE9F930" bold="true" box="[189,315,1638,1664]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Chemistry</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED69CFE7984F7053C40FF9E4FE51F930" box="[330,387,1638,1664]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">TLC</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED69CFE7984F7053C4CAF9E4FE3CF930" box="[399,494,1638,1664]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">HPTLC</collectionCode>
): Sekikaic, hypoprotocetraric and succinprotocetraric (tr.) acids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36204A9984F7053C5F8F908FDC4F95A" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BC75722984F7053C5F8F908FDC4F95A" blockId="28.[136,1452,1462,2087]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C5F8F908FE39F913" bold="true" box="[189,491,1673,1700]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ecology and distribution</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C4B8F90BFD0FF913" authorityName="A. Morales &amp; V. Marcano" authorityYear="2021" box="[509,733,1673,1699]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="anteojina">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C4B8F90BFD0FF913" box="[509,733,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ramalina anteojina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare species in the Venezuelan Andes known from alpine elevations (
<quantity id="4C80FAC7984F7053C44DF92FFEB2F977" box="[264,352,1709,1735]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="4100.0">4100 m</quantity>
) where it is found in paramo, growing on rocks (Fig. 30). This is the 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C12FF92FFAFDF977" box="[1130,1327,1709,1735]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C12FF92FFB05F977" box="[1130,1239,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ramalina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
that grows at the highest altitude in 
<collectingCountry id="F36F17B2984F7053C4D9F952FDC1F95A" box="[412,531,1744,1770]" name="Venezuela" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36204A9984F7053C5F8F971FD23F797" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC75722984F7053C5F8F971FB59F7B4" blockId="28.[136,1452,1462,2087]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C5F8F971FEF8F8BD" bold="true" box="[189,298,1779,1805]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C404F971FDF5F8BD" authorityName="A. Morales &amp; V. Marcano" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,551,1779,1805]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="anteojina">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C404F971FDF5F8BD" box="[321,551,1779,1805]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ramalina anteojina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the erect thallus, striate, with more or less subterete, sorediate branches; elliptic or linear, marginal pseudocyphellae; a very compact cortex; and the presence of sekikaic, hypoprotocetraric and succinprotocetraric acids. 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C785F8BBFC71F8E3" authorityName="A. Morales &amp; V. Marcano" authorityYear="2021" box="[704,931,1849,1875]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="anteojina">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C785F8BBFC71F8E3" box="[704,931,1849,1875]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ramalina anteojina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C04AF8B8FE1BF8C7" authority="(Marcano &amp; Morales 1994 a)" baseAuthorityName="Marcano &amp; Morales" baseAuthorityYear="1994" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tenuissima">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C04AF8B8FA7EF8E3" box="[1295,1452,1850,1875]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">R. tenuissima</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE92AD3984F7053C5D5F8DFFE13F8C7" author="Marcano, V. &amp; Morales, A." box="[144,449,1885,1911]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="26 - 33" refId="ref51417" refString="Marcano, V. &amp; Morales, A. (1994 a) New species of Ramalina from Venezuela. The Bryologist 97: 26 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3243345" type="journal article" year="1994">Marcano &amp; Morales 1994a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Both species are characterized by striate, filamentous laciniae, with linear, longitudinally arranged pseudocyphellae and the presence of sekikaic acid. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C6E6F803FBFEF82A" authorityName="A. Morales &amp; V. Marcano" authorityYear="2021" box="[931,1068,1921,1946]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="anteojina">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C6E6F803FBFEF82A" box="[931,1068,1921,1946]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">R. anteojina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is saxicolous, very small (&lt;
<quantity id="4C80FAC7984F7053C02EF802FA76F82A" box="[1387,1444,1920,1946]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
) and contain additional hypoprotocetraric and succinprotocetraric acids, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C782CA1984F7053C148F826FB77F80D" baseAuthorityName="Marcano &amp; Morales" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[1037,1189,1956,1981]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tenuissima">
<emphasis id="B90C8B30984F7053C148F826FB77F80D" box="[1037,1189,1956,1981]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">R. tenuissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is corticolous, up to 
<quantity id="4C80FAC7984F7053C0CAF821FF78F851" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="32.0">32 cm</quantity>
long and contains only sekikaic acid. The SEM study shows that the upper surface is characterized by a scabrose, disrupted surface, comprising numerous, small, fragmented and flake-like hyphae (Fig. 19).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC75722984F7053C5F8F78FFD23F797" blockId="28.[136,1452,1462,2087]" box="[189,753,2061,2087]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
The name of the species refers to the 
<typeStatus id="54C3E980984F7053C725F78FFD42F797" box="[608,656,2061,2087]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
